ZANZIBAR Government has strongly condemned the incident of a veteran politician, Baraka Mohammed Shamte who was attacked on Monday. According to a statement issued by the Director of Communications, Charles Hillary on Tuesday stated that the politician sustained injuries in different parts of his body and he was immediately rushed to the hospital. According to the statement, the Isles Police Force is conducting a thorough investigation to unmask the perpetrators of the barbaric incident. “The Revolutionary Government of Zanzibar is requesting citizens to be calm since it is handling the matter,” the statement read